  "text": "We analysed the possible functional impact of the KMT2A/MLL1-Msk1 interaction by using a knockdown approach in MEFs. These cells express HoxA genes, known KMT2A/MLL1 targets [CITATION_1] . Transient siRNA-mediated knockdown conditions were established for KMT2A/MLL1, resulting in a >40% reduction in the protein (Fig. 2a) (Fig. 2b ). For Msk1, we established well-tolerated knockdown conditions that reduced Msk1 protein abundance by >90% (Fig. 2c) , whilst leaving protein and transcript levels of its close paralogue Msk2 unaffected (Fig. 2c, d) .",
